{"title": "Do S\u2019poreans look down on local? Price and perception an issue, say aspiring brands", "tags": "singapore", "timestamp": "2023-02-11", "content": "SINGAPORE - Five years ago, fashion designer Joanna Lim was running a pop-up stall at the Boutique Fairs event at the F1 Pit Building when a local customer questioned the value of the dress she was selling, which was priced above $200. The customer compared it with similar-priced clothing from Paris.\nThe 29-year-old founder of local fashion label Joannalsm told The Straits Times she was reminded of the experience, when 17-year-old Zoe Gabriel was shamed online for calling her Charles & Keith bag her \u201cfirst luxury bag\u201d in January."}